annotationA: Dihydropyrimidine dehydrogenase [NADP(+)]; Involved in pyrimidine base degradation. Catalyzes the reduction of uracil and thymine; Belongs to the dihydropyrimidine dehydrogenase family
annotationB: Pyd3 is a beta-alanine synthase involved in pyrimidine catabolism, beta-alanine biosynthesis and cuticle pigmentation
